text: Acestrorhynchus nasutus is a species of fish in the family Acestrorhynchidae. It was described by Carl H. Eigenmann in 1912. It inhabits the Orinoco and Amazon Rivers, as well as rivers in Guyana. It reaches a maximum standard length of . ==References== Category:Acestrorhynchidae Category:Fish described in 1912
